Pre-viewing prediction... No-ish, it wont technically "spoil" with some caveats. Food bourne pathogens require FAT TOM; Food, Acidity, Time, Temperature, Oxygen, and Moisture in varying amounts depending on what type of mold/bacteria it is. That being said Yeast can survive using both aerobic and anaerobic respiration, although the latter is much less efficient, so its difficult for it to "thrive" and form a colony. Also, the absolute most deadly toxin on earth Botulinum prefers low, to zero oxygen like that found in canned goods and "clear smoked" or Carbon Monoxide flushed seafood. These fun facts brought to you by my ServSafe certification, or Hand Washing  License as i like to call it!
